content.description:
Start on the good jugs with your feet under the overhang and stick to the left side of the boulder. Lots of ways to do it, kneebars, crimps, big moves, take your pick. I generally went up and left then followed the diagonal crack to the top. 



From the parking lot head into the forest on an obvious trail facing away from the bay. It will head towards a big slabby section of rock with a trail leading to the top of an exposed section of rock at the peak. Pick your way down and there will be a boulder with "the four horseman" spray painted on it. This boulder is directly to the right with a big overhang to start and nice bulletproof rock the rest of the way up. 

two pads and a spotter

Lots of variations and ways to go about it. All were cruiser and I climbed up and down it several times to warm up. 



Boulder directly left of the one with 'It's fuckin' wimdy" has 'the four horsemen' spray painted on it. 

one or two pads

climbs.name: One mans garbage is another man persons good ungarbage

content.description:
Super low start on slopers, move out right with a cool mantle move and get your feet under you. Head for the top. Rock quality is good but sadly has some gross spray paint on it that detracts from the climb. Movement is fun and way easier than it looks. 



Blue and white rock with 'the lord god' painted on it

pads

Sit start on massive jugs, move straight up the crack and practice those jams! keep moving and mantle over the lip. can surely be done with face holds but who doesnt love a good hand jam boulder?



directly right of 'thuggishly graceful'

one or two pads

Start with both hands on good jugs- there are many to choose from. Head up and right then straight to the top. I avoided the crumbly wet crack and only used face holds. All are thin and super sharp. I broke off a bit from the key hold but the rest appeared to be good stable rock. Hard climbing all the way up. 



Just to the right of 'It's fuckin' wimdy'

one or two pads. spotter unnecessary but helpful

Sit start with hands matched on good incut edges. Right hand goes out to sloping edge and left hand does the same. Head for sloping topout and mantle. All holds are slopey and don't look very good but it flows really well and is surprisingly easy. 



From the set of boulders holding the other at Cook's head left facing the bay, or right facing the soccer fields. it is just around the corner. 

one or two pads.

climbs.name: Two rights don't make a wrong

content.description:
Cruiser of a climb but really fun with good movement. Sit start on jugs and move your way up and right into the beautiful finger crack. get sinking finger locks for the next four or five moves and wish it kept going. Top out and do it a few more times for fun



Directly right of "outside in is inside out"

one or two pads

Crux was figuring out how to start the route. Once you work through it head up to the sloper jug, get your feet and mantle up onto that hold, then top out. Funky movement but fun. Spray paint is a bummer



has '4 ever' spray painted on it

pads
